{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nThe plan-review \"Pass-2 verify\" pass takes the findings the finder raised and makes a decisive\nper-finding \"is this real?\" judgment. There are two problems with how it chunks and where it lives,\nand this epic resolves both together with a clean sequencing.\n\n**Problem 1 — token-naive chunking.** The bespoke verifier chunks the findings list by a HARD-CODED\ncount (`pass2_verify(batch_size=12)`, `passes.py`; `range(0, len(findings), 12)`). It is an arbitrary\nmechanical guardrail (introduced in the original plan-review epic 5fd2, commit 2873a916), never\nconfig-driven, token-naive. The workflow-engine gate (the sole verdict producer since the B-RETIRE\ncutover, commit 68dc9713) instead does ONE aggregate verify call over all findings — correct for the\ncommon case, but a pathological huge-findings ticket could exceed the model context window where the\ncount-12 chunk would not. The principled fix is TOKEN-BASED chunking (estimate the verify request vs\nthe selected model's window — like the Pass-1 finder `sizing.py` machinery already does), splitting\nonly when needed, NOT a magic count.\n\n**Problem 2 — a surviving second code path.** The B-RETIRE cutover deleted the bespoke full-review\norchestrator (`run_review`, the `gate_engine` flag, the B4 parity harness, `pass4_coach`), but\n`pass2_verify` / `verifier_cfg` / `_run_passes` are NOT dead: they back the opt-in **progressive\ndrift-refresh** probe (`verify.progressive_drift_refresh`, default off → `orchestrator.drift_refresh`\n→ `_run_passes` → `pass2_verify`). So there are still TWO verify call sites, which is exactly the \"no\ntwo divergent batching rules\" hazard. Rather than maintain a shared chunker across both, we **migrate\ndrift-refresh onto the workflow engine FIRST**, collapsing to a single verify path; the chunking work\nthen becomes a single-site change.\n\n**Decision — verifier model downgrade becomes a declarative per-step `model:` key.** The bespoke\n`verifier_cfg` downgrades the verify pass from the default frontier model (Opus) to a decisive\nnon-frontier model (Sonnet) UNLESS the operator explicitly chose a model. The workflow verify step\ndoes NOT apply this today (it uses the runner default). We reproduce the downgrade declaratively via\nthe existing per-step `model:` key (`resolve_model`, WS-D3: step > workflow > cfg) so the workflow\nverify step pins Sonnet-by-default with operator override preserved. NOTE: the two historical call\nsites sizing against possibly-different models is NOT a blocker for chunking — each site sizes against\nits own resolved model and both are correct; and after the migration there is only one site anyway.\nBecause this makes a per-step `model:` key first-class on a shipped gate workflow, the change must be\nreflected in the **visual workflow editor UX**: the per-step model must be editable in the properties\npanel and must round-trip through BPMN export/import (today only the workflow-level model is carried,\nso editing the workflow in the visual editor could silently DROP a step's model).\n\n## Workstreams (sequenced)\n\n**WS1 — Migrate drift-refresh onto the workflow engine (FIRST), delete the bespoke pipeline.**\n- Add a \"probe mode\" to the plan-review workflow: run find→verify→decide over a restricted criteria\n  subset (`_PROBE_CRITERIA = E4, G1G2`) instead of the full registry (a `criteria` allowlist input on\n  the finder op, or a dedicated `drift-probe.yaml` reusing the same ops/prompts).\n- Expose per-finding decisions + citations in the workflow return shape so the escalation gate can\n  inspect `decision` and `citations[].path` against the drifted-file set.\n- Rewrite `drift_refresh` to wrap the workflow call; keep the non-LLM orchestration in Python\n  (candidate detection, dep re-hash, escalation gate, `refresh_attestation`, synthetic PASS verdict).\n- Once nothing calls `_run_passes`, DELETE the now-dead bespoke orchestration: `_run_passes`,\n  `pass2_verify`, `verifier_cfg`. Keep the genuinely shared helpers (`pass3_decide`,\n  `pass3_over_findings`, `verify_instructions`, `coach_instructions`, `render_coach_notes`,\n  `load_move_registry`).\n\n**WS2 — Verifier model downgrade as a per-step `model:` key + visual-editor UX.**\n- Pin the workflow verify step's `model:` to the decisive non-frontier verifier (Sonnet) by default,\n  preserving operator override (mirrors `verifier_cfg` semantics declaratively via `resolve_model`).\n- Surface the per-step `model` field in the visual editor properties panel (a select over the known\n  model ladder) and make it round-trip through BPMN export/import so the visual editor never drops a\n  step's model on save.\n- Document the per-step `model:` knob in the workflow-authoring + editor docs.\n\n**WS3 — Principled token-based chunking for the (now single) verify path.**\n- Replace any count-based batching with a token estimate vs the verify step's resolved model window,\n  reusing `sizing.py` `largest_window_tokens(model)` + the `est_tokens` (chars/4) estimator rather\n  than a new magic constant or a new tokenizer dependency.\n- Budget = the verify request (system prompt + `verify_instructions` listing) PLUS projected output,\n  against a named headroom fraction of the window (not the raw window).\n- `<= budget` findings → ONE aggregate verify call (unchanged behavior). `> budget` → minimal\n  principled splits that preserve GLOBAL finding enumeration and re-merge by finding `index` (the\n  existing merge contract).\n- Single-oversized-finding edge case (one finding's text alone exceeds the budget): first escalate the\n  verify model up the ladder (`models_at_or_above`); if it still does not fit, mark that finding\n  INDETERMINATE (non-blocking, surfaced) rather than silently dropping it.\n\n**WS4 — Coach-call parity nit (separate task).**\n- Bespoke `pass4_coach` returns `[]` with NO LLM call when there are 0 surviving advisories; the\n  workflow ALWAYS runs the `coach_notes` prompt step (1 wasted coach call on a clean PASS). Gate the\n  workflow `coach_notes` step on `surviving > 0` (a `when:` condition) to match bespoke.\n\n## Design decisions (resolved)\n\n- **Sequencing:** WS1 (migration) lands before WS3 (chunking) so chunking is a single-site change and\n  \"no two divergent batching rules\" is satisfied by construction, not by a shared helper.\n- **Model downgrade = per-step `model:` key** (declarative, operator-overridable); each verify site\n  sizes against its own resolved model — no cross-path model reconciliation is required.\n- **Editor parity is in scope:** a per-step `model:` on a shipped gate workflow MUST be editable and\n  round-trip-safe in the visual editor (properties panel + BPMN), or editing the workflow there would\n  regress the gate.\n- **Token estimator:** reuse `est_tokens` (chars/4) + `largest_window_tokens`; no new dependency.\n  Budget includes projected output and a headroom fraction, not the raw window.\n- **Merge semantics:** preserve global enumeration; re-merge by finding `index` (existing contract).\n- **Oversized single finding:** escalate model, else INDETERMINATE — never silent-drop.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Drift-refresh runs entirely through the workflow engine; the bespoke `pass2_verify` /\n  `verifier_cfg` / `_run_passes` orchestration is deleted, leaving ONE verify code path.\n- The workflow verify step applies the Sonnet-by-default verifier model (operator override preserved),\n  and that per-step model is fully editable and round-trip-safe in the visual workflow editor.\n- The workflow verify chunks findings into multiple calls ONLY when the estimated request would exceed\n  the resolved model's window (token-based, reusing the sizing/window machinery); small findings sets\n  remain ONE aggregate call with no behavior change.\n- No magic `batch_size` constant remains anywhere; a clean-PASS (0 advisories) makes no coach call.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **WS1:** `drift_refresh` produces its probe verdict via the workflow engine (find→verify→decide\n      over `E4, G1G2`), not `_run_passes`; the non-LLM orchestration (candidate detection, dep re-hash,\n      escalation on a blocking finding or a finding citing a drifted file, `refresh_attestation`)\n      is preserved and covered by tests.\n- [ ] **WS1:** The workflow return shape exposes per-finding `decision` + `citations[].path` at the\n      granularity the drift escalation gate requires.\n- [ ] **WS1:** `_run_passes`, `pass2_verify`, and `verifier_cfg` are DELETED; shared helpers\n      (`pass3_decide`, `pass3_over_findings`, `verify_instructions`, coach/move helpers) remain and are\n      still used by the workflow ops. No dead bespoke orchestration remains.\n- [ ] **WS2:** The workflow verify step pins the decisive non-frontier verifier model (Sonnet) by\n      default and honors an explicit operator model override (parity with the old `verifier_cfg`),\n      resolved via the existing per-step `model:` / `resolve_model` path.\n- [ ] **WS2:** The visual editor properties panel lets a user view/edit a step's `model`, and a\n      per-step `model` survives a BPMN export → import (visual-edit → save) round-trip unchanged; a\n      regression test asserts the round-trip. Authoring + editor docs document the per-step `model:`\n      knob.\n- [ ] **WS3:** A token estimate (no magic `batch_size` constant) decides verify chunking, reusing\n      `largest_window_tokens` + `est_tokens`; the budget accounts for the verify request plus projected\n      output against a named headroom fraction of the resolved model window.\n- [ ] **WS3:** `<= budget` findings → one aggregate verify call (unchanged); `> budget` → minimal\n      principled splits that preserve global enumeration and re-merge verifications by finding `index`.\n      A test exercises a `> budget` findings set (via a deterministic window-shrink seam) and asserts\n      principled splitting, NOT count-12.\n- [ ] **WS3:** A single finding larger than the budget escalates the verify model up the ladder and,\n      if still too large, is marked INDETERMINATE (non-blocking, surfaced) — never silently dropped; a\n      test covers this path.\n- [ ] **WS4:** The workflow `coach_notes` step is gated on `surviving > 0`; a 0-advisory PASS makes no\n      coach LLM call (bespoke parity), covered by a test.\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make check` + the full test suite pass.\n","title":"Workflow Pass-2 verify: migrate drift-refresh off bespoke, add per-step model key (editor-surfaced) + principled token-based chunking"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782580848821591001,"uuid":"35f2ba73-b791-4c7a-8ca3-875c92b33d8f"}